The paper deals with the problem of overconfidence in machine learning models when faced with test samples from an unknown distribution. This is a common problem in various subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given that the paper focuses on image classification and proposes methods specifically for improving image confidence, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant as they deal with related topics such as uncertainty modeling and novelty detection.
